node.text: DIY an upholstered wingback headboard for $80

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Angela Rose | DIY and Design on August 31, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and indoor.

node.text:
Hallway done (swipe)! But was it all worth it?…the shiplap that is almost entirely covered…the giant art frame I made up and the frustration while hanging it…the non-wired lights (magic puck lights🙌🏻)…?

I say YES! WORTH IT! and to think that this hallway space has been entire forgotten for 5 years, and is now such a relaxing focal point and it pulls together everything downstairs so well (swipe to see all the angles!).

Did you see it with the cabinets?
With the fireplace?
Looking into the kitchen?
At night?
😍😍😍

*my helper insisted on getting in the photo with me🤣. I will post her outtakes tonight😉. She is somethin else🤣.

node.text:
OPERATION: giant planter to block ugly view…complete! I didn’t realize how much that cinderblock view out my windows was making me sad…until I built THIS to cover it up! Total game changer. 

Yes, I painted wood and added fake plants (with REAL dirt) which upset some of you, BUT we can still love each other…because we ALL can relate to the floating basketball hoop in the pool(🤣see stories).

Stay tuned for stories to see how you can see this view from practically EVERYWHERE in my house!

node.text:
Operation garage SNAZZY-ify complete, and just in time for the kids to feel a little inspired going back to school. We battle a lot of anxiety in this house, me included…and this quote really spoke to me for how I want to set the tone for them for this year. It’s not until we actually take that leap (and potentially fall)…in order to realize we can fly. Painting this giant quote wall and redoing my floors was just the refresh I needed (I have wanted to epoxy my floors #sponsored since we moved in 6 years ago!). 

To my kids: I know you are scared. You haven’t been in a normal class for a year and a half. I know how hard you work to battle and manage your anxiety, and I’m so proud of how brave you are. You’ve dealt with a LOT of changes this past year. Remember, the bravest people are those who are scared and STILL try. Reach out to the kid by themselves on the playground and be a friend. I know YOU feel like it’s hard to make friends, but chances are others are nervous too and you can be THAT friend to others. Be kind and find things in common. You got this!

Love,
Mom

And for me…I spend so much time in my garage, and it’s always been such an eyesore. Now that I have these @rustoleum EpoxyShield floors, I feel like it gives me more creative space to breathe and create! Totally worth it, and I am so excited with how they turned out! #prideinthemaking

I can FINALLY share what I was filming for!…my first ever commercial partnering with Omaze to announce your chance to win THIS gorgeous 2.6 million dollar dream home in Miami (or take the cash option of 1.8 million dollars). I know😳, I think it’s freaking cool too and I can’t believe I got to be a part of it (swipe for more photos and awkward poses😉).

And my favorite part, every donation supports Make A Wish @makeawishamerica , one of my favorite non profits that is near and dear to my heart. 

Filming all the content for this dream home was honestly, a dream come true…thanks for being excited with me!

And…
If you want to enter for your chance to win this Dream Home (and if you win, invite me over!), click the link in my bio or go to omaze.com/angelarose.
**use my code ANGELA300 when you enter for an extra 300 entries🙌🏻.
@omaze #ad

node.text:
KITCHEN reveal part 3: the view that made me cry😭. Those shelves you guys!!! How was I on the fence about them??? They are the perfect finale to this kitchen. Standing from this view and seeing that stormy backsplash, the @smegusa range, the soft fluffy brick, the painted black windows, the custom island, the DIY hood, the shelves…I love it. Every detail. 

Deep breath. What’s your favorite feature? And can you spot the funny thing I added???

Speaking of details:

Appliances: 48” dual fuel @smegusa Portofino Range in stainless steel (5 gas burners). 24” Fully Integrated Panel Ready @smegusa Dishwasher (to keep dishwasher hidden with a panel) #MySMEGKitchen #SMEGpartner

Cabinets: I kept existing boxes and refaced with custom door fronts in Angela Rose Slim Shaker Dream Dusk from @nieucabinetdoors 

Countertops: Danby marble (sourced from Vermont)
